I’ll fight to see the Survivors' Bill of Rights Act signed into law. It's an important step toward empowering survivors. #IHaveTheRightTo
Good luck to the @Patriots against Arizona in the season opener tonight! #GoPats
So grateful for our men and women in uniform and all those who have served and sacrificed in defense of our nation.

We will never forget the thousands of lives lost 15 years ago today or the brave men & women who saved so many. #NeverForget
@DWCeagles is an important part of the Nashua community. I'm working with Mayor Donchess to find a solution to support @DWCeagles & students
On #LaborDay we thank the American workers who are the foundation of the US. They will continue to grow our economy & a strong middle class.
Great news that the US & China have joined the #ParisAgreement. Critical step toward addressing #climatechange & protecting our planet

Sexual assault is far too prevalent on college campuses. Proud to work with @ksc_web & Keene community to promote student safety.

Thank you to our community health centers, who provide critical healthcare services to Granite State families and communities. #NHCW16

Proud to help pass a bill to help ensure veterans’ benefits go up when the gov makes cost-of-living adjustments!
Glad the House passed a bill I cosponsored to strengthen financial counseling for students & families. Let’s make #HigherEd more accessible!
I agree with Speaker Ryan; we need to work together to end all types of gun violence aimed at harming innocent members of our community.
Congress should focus on promoting #equality, instead @GOPoversight is holding anti-#LGBT hearing on anniversary of #PulseShooting #shame
FACT: 91% of suspected terrorists on the terror watch list who sought guns in 2015 were approved.  #DisarmHate
Horrified by unfolding attack in Istanbul – we must strengthen cooperation with our allies to stop terror
We can and must protect the 2nd amendment while keeping guns out of the hands of terrorists to prevent tragedies like Orlando
Happy birthday, NH! Today is the 228th anniversary of New Hampshire’s statehood. The Granite State was the 9th to join the Union. #NHHistory
Proud to help spread the courageous words of the Stanford rape victim on the House floor. Tune in now to CSPAN to watch #WeAreAllEmilyDoe
Shameful that House Republicans refuse to consider HR 1076, a bill that would keep dangerous firearms out of the hands of known terrorists
To the families of the victims of this heartbreaking attack, and to #LGBT communities everywhere: we stand with you. #OrlandoUnited
Thank you to our service members, today and every day, for your courage and sacrifice protecting our nation.
#DoYourJob, @SpeakerRyan! Cancel recess so we can get to work on meaningful solutions for urgent public health crises!
The current aerial tramway at @cannonmountain opened 36 years ago today! The original was the first of its kind in the US. #NHHistory
Very disappointed by defeat of @RepSeanMaloney’s amndmt. No one should be discriminated against because of who they love! #WeAreWithYou
Shameful that House Republicans changed their votes to deny LGBT equality. #WhippingforInequality

Today 2nd District resident Susan & I spoke w/ @fox25news re. the importance of sharing stories of families hurt by addiction-Watch at 5:30!

Tonight I’ll be hosting my 11th telephone town hall! If you’re interested in participating, please call 603-226-1002 for more information

Congrats to @FPUniversity, @AllianceFiresee, and the @NHArt on receiving grants from the National Endowment for the Arts! #ArtWorks
This week is #NationalSmallBusinessWeek. We’re lucky to have so many great small business leaders in NH. You are an invaluable resource!
Congrats to Patrick Kaplo from Windham H.S. on being named #PBSDigitalInnovator for leading the classroom in the #edtech space.
Today NH remembers the Old Man of the Mountain. He’s been gone 13 years but lives on as the iconic symbol of New Hampshire! #LiveFreeOrDie
Happy Teacher Appreciation Day! Thank you to all our wonderful educators in the Granite State! #ThankATeacher #TeacherAppreciationDay
Honored 2 congratulate Gen Lori Robinson, UNH alum named one of @Time's most influential ppl &nominated to be 1st female combatant commander
Proud to have led the fight against the Kinder Morgan NED pipeline, and so pleased the project has been suspended. Big win for NH.  #NED
Proud to cosponsor the 100 Years of Women in Congress Act to honor the first woman elected to serve in Congress, Jeannette Rankin!
About 20,000 Americans are living with #hemophelia. I stand with our hemophilia patients and caregivers on #WHD2016.
The #wagegap affects women of all ages, races, and education levels. We must do better. #EqualPayDay
On average, women earn $0.79 to a man’s dollar. I’m proud to show my support for #EqualPayDay and to fight for pay equity. #EqualPayCantWait

Thanks to @TheNC for 20 years of reducing teen pregnancy, and giving girls and women the power to decide their future. #TheNC20
Glad the Pres. has proposed new steps to address opioid epidemic. But we must do more to increase funding for states fighting this crisis!
Everyone in our office is safe; sincere thanks to the Capitol Police officers for their brave actions today and every day
As a U.S. Ambassador, @WallyBrewster deserves fair & equal treatment at home AND abroad. RT to show your support. #ImWithWally
As #SCOTUS hears a case that could strip away reproductive rights, we must unite to protect access to affordable contraception #HandsOffMyBC
So proud that last night, legislation I cosponsored to honor our prisoners of war and those missing in action passed the U.S. House of Reps.
My Workforce Development Investment Act would help community colleges partner w businesses to offer crucial skill training for our students!
Proud to celebrate #InternationalWomensDay and to continue fighting for a world where women & girls have equal rights & opportunity #IWD2016
Proud to celebrate Women’s History Month with General Vaught, President of the Women In Military Service For America Memorial Foundation!

Call my Concord office at 603-226-1002 for call-in info if you'd like to join my 10th telephone town hall this Wednesday!
Proud to be a cosponsor of the Female Veteran Suicide Prevention Act, which recently passed the House #PreventVetSuicide
Honored to receive a perfect score from @AAUWActionFund for my work in Congress. Let’s keep working together on behalf of women & families!
Honored to receive an “A” on this year’s @NEAToday report card! Look forward to continuing to work to expand access to quality #education.
Proud to stand with the #ProChoice caucus in calling for the disbanding of the Select Panel investigating #PlannedParenthood
Ensuring working women are supported by adequate family leave policies is a critical step towards ensuring #equalpay
Women of color in #NH and across the country often face an even wider #wagegap when it comes to #equalpay for #equalwork. #EqualPayCantWait
The fight for #equalpay is not over. Data shows that women still only make 78 cents to a man’s dollar for the same work #equalpaycantwait

Today we honor those lost at #PearlHarbor 74 years ago and all those who rose to defend our nation in response to the infamous attack
Voted this week to reauthorize #ESEA. Look forward to continuing to work toward an #education system that meets needs of all #NH students!
On this Veterans Day, and every day, we give thanks to our veterans for all they have done to protect this great nation.
Just introduced the Small Business Growth Through Exports Act, to help #NH companies compete globally. Let’s keep working for #smallbiz!
Shocked and appalled by today’s vandalism at the Claremont Planned Parenthood office. I stand with @PPFA today and every day.
My thoughts and prayers are with the victims of today's shooting in Oregon. Our nation must do more to prevent future tragedies.
Huge congrats to the students & teachers at Canaan Elementary School on being named a 2015 Blue Ribbon School by the US Dept. of Education
As a cosponsor, I was proud to support the #NASPER Reauthorization Act as it passed the House yesterday evening
My heart goes out to the families and loved ones of Alison and Adam of @WDBJ7 in VA, lost this morning to an unconscionable act of violence.
Thinking of my father and all those who protect our nation as we commemorate 70 years since the end of #WWII. #VJDay
#SocialSecurity has helped millions of Americans lead healthy, stable lives for 80 yrs. I remain committed to protecting this vital program.
Thank you, today and everyday, to all of our brave men and women who have served and sacrificed for our nation. #PurpleHeartDay
Today we commemorate 50 years of the Voting Rights Act and rededicate ourselves to protecting #votingrights for all Americans. #VRA50
All Americans deserve #paidleave, regardless of where you live or work. That’s why I support the #FAMILYAct
Proud to celebrate #FMLA22 today, but it’s time we ensure all workers & families can access #paidleave. #FAMILYAct
#LWCF has preserved our natural & cultural heritage for 50 yrs. We must reauthorize this essential tool for conserving iconic #publiclands
Today, I discussed how we can attract students towards careers in #organic farming during an Agriculture Committee hearing.
Happy Fourth of July! Hope everyone is having fun celebrating our nation's founding with your friends, family, and loved ones!
THRILLED #SCOTUS has ruled in favor of equality for all; Finally every American can marry the person they love!
Glad the #SCOTUS decision today will prevent millions of Americans from losing their health insurance! #KingvBurwell
The #ExIm Bank helps dozens of #NH businesses compete in the global marketplace – it’s time to reauthorize! #HoldAVote #ExIm4Jobs
Proud to discuss ways to improve intl food aid policy to better save taxpayer $$ and help those in need during Ag Committee hearing today!
Congrats to Katherine Fish of Bethlehem's Profile School for being selected to participate in the @librarycongress Summer Teacher Institute!
Great to see Granite State native Hawk Jensen’s “Witness Project” films shown at the Library of Congress this week!
Proud to work with @RepMaloney & Rep. @PeteSessions, & a bipartisan coalition to introduce legislation to help fund breast cancer research!
I questioned VA officials on improving the inefficient procurement process for non-VA care. Our #veterans deserve the highest quality care!
Today, we honor our nation's veterans and vow to repay our debt to them for their courageous service!
Proud to help pass the Ruth Moore Act in the VA committee to help survivors of military sexual trauma receive the services they need!
Proud the House came together to pass the BRAVE Act, a bill I helped introduce to increase veteran employment opportunities!
Happy 50th anniversary to Head Start! Early childhood education is critical to helping NH families thrive. #HeadStart50
Last night I joined the NH Police Association to honor the memory of Officer Stephen Arkell. Thanks to first responders for keeping us safe!
Questioned VA officials on egregious purchase card cost overruns; every cent should be going towards improving health outcomes for our vets!

Great to visit the VA Medical Center in White River Junction to hear about their efforts to provide care to our brave vets.
As #SCOTUS hears opening arguments on #MarriageEquality, we trumpet the rights of all citizens to marry who they love! #LoveCantWait
Happy Arbor Day! NH is the 2nd most forested state in the country & our trees are critical to our economy & landscape.
Glad the Senate finally came together to pass legislation to combat human trafficking & confirm Loretta Lynch as our next Attorney General!
Proud my amendment to protect the interests of veteran, women, and minority entrepreneurs passed with strong bipartisan support – 244 to 173
Last night was a big win for #energyefficiency! Glad the House passed a bipartisan bill that will reduce energy consumption & create jobs.
Good luck to all of the runners in the #BostonMarathon today! #BostonStrong
Happy National Volunteer week! Always inspiring to see people taking time out of their busy lives to support their communities. #NVW2015
The #LWCF helps protect everything from national parks to wildlife refuges; proud to help introduce a bipartisan bill to make it permanent!
Two years after the tragic attack at the Boston Marathon, we honor those who were lost and send our prayers to their loved ones.
Today marks a year since Boko Haram kidnapped nearly 300 schoolgirls in Nigeria; we must keep working to stop this evil terrorist group.
Proud to work with @RepBlainePress to end redundant mailings to bank & credit union customers; R's and D's should work together to cut waste
With a guilty verdict in the Boston Marathon bombing trial, thoughts & prayers are with the families & friends of the victims. #BostonStrong
A year after #McCutcheon, dark money still controls our elections. We must restore democracy & ensure the voices of all Americans are heard!
My bill renamed the Nashua Air Traffic Control Center after longtime employee Patty Clark; congrats on her 52nd anniversary of service!
Glad @SenatorShaheen's energy efficiency legislation passed the Senate; I will continue working to pass this common sense bill in the house!
Proud to support the Accelerating the End of Breast Cancer Act to help fight breast cancer with research and treatment!
Proud to help reintroduce the Paycheck Fairness Act to help eliminate the gender pay gap and ensure pay equity for every American.
Proud to help introduce the HOPE for Alzheimer’s Act to fight this terrible disease by expanding research and improving treatment.
Glad FEMA funding was approved to help NH repair damage from recent extreme weather. Proud to work with the full delegation to secure it.
Thoughts and prayers are with the loved ones of the passengers & crew on Germanwings Flight 9525. Deeply saddened by this tragedy.
Happy St. Patrick’s Day, everyone! Have fun and be safe!
Proud to join 11 of my colleagues to call on the VA to improve health care services offered for female veterans after they return home.
Congrats to the team from @ASDNHorg in Nashua on winning the Regional Science Bowl. Good luck at the National Finals! #STEM
Congrats to Jennifer McNail of Littleton on being named a veteran caregiver advocate through the Elizabeth Dole Foundation Fellows program!
Over the weekend, we celebrated #InternationalWomensDay & the strides women have taken toward achieving equality around the world!
This weekend, we commemorate the historic march in Selma - we must never stop fighting for equality and justice for all.
Proud to help introduce a bill to make the American Opportunity Tax Credit permanent so all students can pursue their dreams!
Proud to help reintroduce bipartisan legislation to help combat sexual assault on campus!
Happy birthday to my good friend @GovernorHassan!
Proud to join a bipartisan call for a long-term transportation bill to fix our infrastructure, create jobs, and spur economic growth!
Very pleased that FairPoint and workers reached a tentative agreement – great news for the Granite State!
Pleased the Clay Hunt Act was signed into law – I helped introduce this bill last year to improve access to mental health care for our vets.
Excited that former NH House Speaker @TerieNorelli will be taking over as President and CEO of the @NHWomensFndn!
Yesterday, I questioned VA Secretary McDonald on cuts to the Choice Card program; we must ensure our vets get the quality care they deserve!
Proud to cosponsor the bipartisan All-American Flag Act to ensure the federal gov’t only purchase flags that are made right here in the USA!

text: Proud to introduce legislation today to close loopholes in House rules and limit special interest access in Congress.
Proud to help introduce legislation to expand access to affordable contraception for women in the military!
On #WorldCancerDay, we renew our fight for a cure. We must work together to end this disease that affects too many people around the world!
Pleased the Senate passed the #ClayHunt SAV Act today – was proud to help introduce this bill 2 improve mental health services for #veterans
Proud to join my Republican colleague Jackie Walorski to reintroduce our bill extending travel benefits to victims of MST.
Game Day!! Let's go #Patriots - we're all rooting for you here in NH!!
Thrilled to attend the 1st hearing of the VA Subcommittee on Health on the cost of vets health care - we must serve those who served us!
Happy birthday to my friend @SenatorShaheen, a great advocate for New Hampshire!
On Holocaust Remembrance Day, we remember those who died and renew our commitment to peace and tolerance.
Proud to help reintroduce the Gov’t by the People Act to stem the tide of dark money into our elections since #CitizensUnited #GetMoneyOut
On the 42nd Anniversary of Roe V. Wade, proud to defend women’s health & rights by cosponsoring Women’s Health Protection Act. #ActForWomen
Glad Shaheen-Portman Act 2 improve energy efficiency, save $, & protect the enviro passed; need more smart, bipartisan plans like this one!
In NH & around the country, we must help #FamiliesSucceed by supporting paid family leave for our workers!
On the 5th anniversary of Citizens United, I am supporting the Democracy for All Amendment to #GetMoneyOut
We must continue to fight to strengthen our middle class, create more jobs for our workers, and make college more affordable #SOTU
Thrilled to help reintroduce the Partnership to Build America Act today to rebuild our nation’s infrastructure and create good jobs.
Exciting news from the Supreme Court!  Looking forward to celebrating full #marriageequality across the US in a few short months!
Good news re. 252,000 new U.S. jobs in December; must keep working to strengthen NH economy!
Proud to help pass the Hire More Heroes Act, which will help small businesses employ more of our nation’s veterans!
Steph Riley was a courageous and compassionate Granite Stater who touched so many lives. My prayers are with her family and friends.
While it was good to see NH’s unemployment rate fall to 4.1% in November, we must continue working to boost economic growth & job creation.
Happy Hanukkah to all my Jewish friends and neighbors celebrating tonight!
Today marks 40 years since the Safe Drinking Water Act became law, protecting the public health nationwide. We must continue these efforts!
On the 70th anniversary of the Battle of the Bulge, we honor the courageous service members who fought for our country in WWII.
Happy Bill of Rights Day! 223 years after the Bill of Rights was ratified, we should remember the civil liberties we have as Americans.
Happy to help pass legislation today to support breast cancer education & prevention efforts among young women.
Proud to help pass the bipartisan Clay Hunt Act, which I helped introduce to address veteran suicide and improve mental health services.
Yesterday, I was proud to help pass the bipartisan ABLE Act, which will help provide financial security for people with disabilities.
At a VA hearing today, I pushed VA officials and Congress to improve the Family Caregiver Program so more NH vets can recuperate at home.
Small biz is the backbone of our economy - let's show support for our local, New Hampshire small businesses on #SmallBusinessSaturday!
Happy Thanksgiving to you and yours. Wishing every Granite Stater the best during this great celebration of our nation’s beginnings!
At today’s VA Subcommittee hearing, I joined my colleagues and VSOs to discuss approaches to improving support services for our veterans.
Great to see NH’s unemployment rate drop to 4.2% in October. We need to continue to work to support economic growth and job creation.
Happy #EntrepreneursDay 2014! Entrepreneurship has a rich tradition in New Hampshire - I am proud to work on behalf of our small businesses.
Excited to see progress on marriage equality in Kansas. Every American should have the freedom to marry the person they love!
This morning, I questioned VA officials about the implementation of the bipartisan VA reform law. We must improve access to care for vets!
On Veterans Day, we honor our heroic veterans, service members, & military families; thank you for your patriotism, service, and sacrifice.
Sad to learn of David Nixon’s passing. He was a great Senate President and a devoted community leader. His loss will be felt all across NH.
My thoughts and prayers are with Tom Menino’s family and friends during this sad time. He was a great mayor and a wonderful man.
Honored to celebrate with Easter Seals NH at the Salute Our Soldiers Breakfast!  Thank you for all your work for NH vets and their families.
Deeply saddened by the tragic events at Marysville-Pilchuck High School in WA; my thoughts and prayers are with the families of the victims.
Horrified by the news today out of Ottawa. My thoughts and prayers are with the fallen soldier, his family, and the people of Canada.
I will be cosponsoring #HRes620 to help our #MarineHeldInMexico #BringBackOurMarine
On National Minimum Wage Day, we urge Congress to raise the wage because no American who works hard should live in poverty #RaiseTheWage
Congrats to Malala Yousafzai and Kailash Satyarthi on receiving the #NobelPeacePrize for improving children’s rights in Pakistan and India.
Congrats to @ExImBankUS for generating $675 million for taxpayers:  reducing deficit by supporting U.S. exports, manufacturing, and jobs.
Today I was proud to join colleagues from both parties to call on pro sports commissioners to work to prevent domestic violence. #DVAM2014
Excited #SCOTUS cleared the path for #marriageequality in five more states. Every American should be able to marry the person they love.
Proud to support the Manufacturing Reinvestment Account Act to help small manufacturers throughout New Hampshire continue to grow.
Proud to support the Unified Savings and Accountability Act to save taxpayer $ by cutting duplication and waste in the federal government.
Honored to take part in WIC's 40th Anniversary Celebration today in Concord. 4 decades of supporting vulnerable women, infants and children!
Congrats to the @NHDES for receiving the Secretary of Defense Freedom Award for exceptional support for Guard & Reserve employees!
I applaud the UN Security Council for approving a resolution to crack down on assistance to terrorist groups like ISIL.
L'Shanah Tovah to my Jewish friends and neighbors! Wishing you all a happy and healthy New Year.
Helped introduce a bill to save taxpayer dollars, cut gov’t waste, and boost accountability by filling open Inspector General positions.
Happy to help introduce the FRUGAL Act yesterday to save taxpayer money by reducing duplication and increasing government efficiency.
Congrats to Dr. Alicia Harvey-Smith on her inauguration as the new president of River Valley Community College in Claremont today!
22 veterans a day die from suicide. We must work to ensure vets with #PTSD & #TBI get the care they deserve. #Stop22aDay
Disappointed the Senate blocked @SenWarren’s bill to lower interest rates on student loan debt , which I helped introduce in the House.
Excited the House passed the Revitalize American Manufacturing and Innovation Act last night to boost the American manufacturing sector!
Disappointed the Senate voted down #PaycheckFairness legislation yesterday 52-40. We must ensure women receive #EqualPay for equal work!
Tomorrow marks 20 years since #VAWA was signed into law. We must continue to support survivors and work to end domestic violence for good!
Proud to help file an amicus brief to the Supreme Court in support of pregnant women’s rights to basic accommodations in the workplace.
Proud to help advance the Ask Veterans Act in yesterday’s VA Committee hearing to ensure veterans receive the quality care they deserve.
On the 13th anniversary of 9/11, our nation remembers those we lost on that terrible day. We remain a people united and strong #neverforget
Thrilled the Senate advanced debate on #PaycheckFairness. It’s time to close the wage gap & ensure women receive #EqualPay for equal work.
On World Suicide Prevention Day, we reaffirm our commitment to providing resources and support for people living with mental illness.
Honored to receive the Golden Triangle award from @NFUtweets and @NewEnglandFU last night! Proud to represent NH small farmers.
Proud to help advocate for the TIGER grant for Sarah Mildred Long Bridge replacement; project will provide a big boost to the NH economy!
Pleased the Senate advanced a Constitutional Amendment to limit political spending; Congress must work to restore the voices of individuals!
Proud to join colleagues to urge Senate leadership to vote on bipartisan anti-human trafficking bills; we must end this barbaric practice.
Thanks for the birthday wishes! @WhipHoyer @RepSinema @NHCAforAction @WomensPolicyInc @AAUWPolicy
This week marks the Land and Water Conservation Fund’s 50th birthday! For 50 years, the LWCF has protected our natural and cultural heritage
Great visit to @NHHEAF today in Concord. Thanks for all you do to expand access to higher ed & help students & families navigate the process
Happy Labor Day! Today we honor and thank America's workers for their strong work ethic and commitment to our national ideals.
Great visit today to the Keene VA clinic and Keene Vet Center. Pleased to know Monadnock Region vets are getting the care they deserve.
Great to meet with Judge Leary, prosecutors, and public defenders yesterday in Nashua to hear more about the Vets Behavioral Health Track.
Today is #WomensEqualityDay. Women still make on avg 77¢ for every 1$ earned by men. All Granite Staters deserve #EqualPay for equal work
Happy 98th birthday to the National Park Service! Almost 100 years of keeping our National Parks spectacular.
I’m hosting a Vets Job Fair Wed., Aug. 27, from 10 to 1 at Harbor Homes in Nashua. Join us to learn about opportunities for vets around NH!
Congrats to Mo’ne Davis and the Taney Dragons for their LLWS run. Great to see such a talented female athlete excelling on the nat’l stage!
James Foley's horrific murder was committed by truly evil individuals who must be brought to justice.My thoughts & prayers are w/ his family
My thoughts & prayers are w/ the family of Senator Jim Jeffords, whose dedication 2 serving the American people will never be forgotten.
On the 79th anniversary of Social Security, I remain committed to always protecting this program that so many NH seniors rely on.
Met w/Father Nelson in Berlin 2 hear his concerns re targeting of Christians in Iraq; must bring together intl. community 2 end the massacre
Tragic news about Robin Williams’ passing. One of the most talented performers of our time, who brought joy to so many people.
My thoughts & prayers are w/ the family of former PSNH President Gary Long, whose commitment to serving the people of NH was truly admirable
Troubling that Market Basket is cutting hours for part time workers; the company must consider the impact on working families.
Proud that the comprehensive VA bill became law today; this is a huge step towards making sure NH vets get the care they need and deserve.
49 yrs after Voting Rights Act's signing, we recommit to the promise that all Americans deserve to have their voices heard. #voterprotection
So relieved that Meriam Ibrahim and her family returned safely to NH. Her courage is an inspiration.
Proud to support the Documents for Continued Safety Act to help domestic violence survivors get ID documents after they flee their abusers.
49 years ago today President Johnson signed #Medicare & #Medicaid into law, guaranteeing health coverage for millions of Americans.
Glad the Senate passed bill 2 save Highway Trust Fund 4 rest of this yr. @SpeakerBoehner please bring it for a vote in the House this week!
After Bob McDonald’s confirmation as VA Secretary, I urge him to work with me and my colleagues to end widespread mismanagement at the VA.
No vet should ever wait for health care; I urge my colleagues in the both houses to pass the comprehensive VA reform bill immediately.
So glad Abby Hernandez is home safe in North Conway. Thanks to the law enforcement officials who protect our communities.
Proud to support @senwarren’s proposal to lower student loan interest rates-we must make college more affordable for Granite State families!
Great to participate in Small Biz hearing on SBIR and STTR Programs; we must continue to support tech innovation for small businesses in NH!
All House members, like Senators, should undergo annual ethics trainings-  I cosponsored a bill today requiring these essential trainings.
Today I signed onto legislation to help stop human trafficking-We must stop this heinous practice, which can occur right in our own backyard
Pleased to join colleagues from both parties to pass H.R.4450 to reauthorize Brand USA and boost tourism across New Hampshire!
Today marks #100Days since the Nigerian schoolgirls' kidnapping. RT if you care. #BringBackOurGirls #JoinRepWilson
Proud Exec.Order was signed today to protect fed. workers from discrimination based on gender identity or sexual orientation #equalityforall
Proud to honor Nashua’s own Staff Sgt. Ryan Pitts at the White House today, where he was awarded the Medal of Honor for heroism.
This week marks 3 months since the kidnapping of over 200 Nigerian schoolgirls. We must #BringBackOurGirls #JoinRepWilson
My thoughts & prayers are with the victims of the tragedy in Ukraine and their families.
Today I helped introduce the Save III Act to cut wasteful gov’t programs; will boost efficiency and save $102 billion over 10 years #SaveAct
Voted for bill to replenish Highway Trust Fund and fund crucial projects like I-93 expansion through next May; we need a long-term solution!
Proud to help introduce a constitutional amendment to reform the campaign finance system & restore power to everyday Americans!
